   "beat_id": "B03",
   "act": "STM TUNNELING — RUN",
   "narration_text": "Run it. Two checks. First: the slope. On the semi-log plot the teal curve is a straight line. Its slope reads minus two kappa — approximately minus two-point-zero-four inverse angstroms. Every extra angstrom of gap multiplies the log-current by that slope. Second: the seven-point-four markers. The two crimson dots — one angstrom apart — show a current ratio of e-squared, approximately seven-point-four. That is Binnig and Rohrer's rule: pull the tip back by one angstrom and the current falls by a factor of seven. The periodic table of surface atoms is built on that sensitivity.",
